                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 303.) I met the prisoner in the Lea Bridge-road about eight o'clock, on the 9th of April, with this saw and square—I asked what he had got—he said he had bought it—I asked him Where—he said in Sun-street, Bishopsgate, about eighteen months ago.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I went to Woodford to look for work; as I was coming down Snaresbrook I met a carpenter, whom I had never seen be<lb></lb>fore; he had the square and saw, and asked me to buy them, which I did, for 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; when I found the name on the square it confounded me; I did hot know what to do; I thought I would take it to Bow, and send it to Mr. Wildsmith; I was never in trouble before.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
